posts.cooked: I just joined the Frc group and I want to help with the software in this group. We will use Java. Any advice you can give me? What should I learn first? What are the basic sections I need to learn?

posts.name: Nelson Green (1108 Mentor Coach Electrical Programming)
posts.cooked:
Here was my getting started list.  You would swap #6 for your team code.  I‚Äôd maybe add reviewing some of Controls lessons here .  I‚Äôd also add these lesson plans as some good steps for FRC .

Our robot code is Java . Learn basics (also CodeAcademy.com and Think Java )

Learn git

Read the docs: docs.wpilib.org

Access the API for details: Overview (WPILib API 2024.3.2)

Learn WPIlib Command-Based

Clone repo at github.com/frc1108

Utilize Example Code

Learn 3rd party libraries: Phoenix (Falcon/ CTRE ) , REVlib (Spark Max) , Monologue, PathPlanner, etc.

Utilize FRC community like tutorial videos and asking Discord or ChiefDelphi

Practice using public code to expand what you know.

Ask for help on public FRC Discord, PhotonVision Discord, ChiefDelphi.
